Solution 4.18. If $\mathfrak{u}^{\mu}$ is the 4-velocity of the conducting element, then the $\underline{\mathbf{E}}$ field seen by charge carriers in the conducting element is $\mathbf{E}^{\mu} = \mathbf{F}_{
u}^{\mu} \mathfrak{u}^{
u}$ . A vector which reduces to $\underline{\mathbf{J}}$ in the rest frame of the charge carriers is $\mathbf{J}^{\mu} + \mathfrak{u}^{\mu} \mathbf{J}_{
u} \mathfrak{u}^{
u}$ . Ohm's equation can then be written as$\mathbf{J}^{\mu} + \mathfrak{u}^{\mu}\mathbf{J}_{
u}\mathfrak{u}^{
u} = \sigma \mathbf{F}_{
u}^{\mu}\mathfrak{u}^{
u}$ . Since this is a tensor equation and is correct in the rest frame of the conducting element, it must be correct in all frames.
